metadata.name: Pages From A Redacted Document #49
metadata.description:
In a time of mistrust, fear and corruption this work looks to reflect how transparency and accountability are removed from those with responsibility with a simple black line.

An abstract representation of the murky world that lurks behind the corridors of power. Kept there hidden and away from the masses.  We demand more.

A representation of documents printed and hand written, that are augmented with highlighters and blocking out pens.

press 'S' to download the hi-res version, which will show the full detail.

metadata.name: Ersbla #207
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Fractal Painting #468
metadata.description:
This is composition art based on mathematics fractal.

Color Pallet has 10 variations.
Frame Line has 2 variations.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
- Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
- Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4800 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js

metadata.name: Excavation #73
metadata.description:
"Excavation" reconstructs the digital screen as a thickened, palimpsestuous ground. Elements are uncovered through an archaeological survey of this ground, while others remain buried beneath layers of digital sediment.

Coded in p5.js.

metadata.name: The Arcimboldo Project #7
metadata.description:
A tribute to Giuseppe Arcimboldo (1526 - 1593), an Italian painter best known for creating imaginative portrait heads made entirely of objects such as fruits, vegetables and flowers.

This token is made of a combination of 192 layers (24 layers x 8 fruits/vegetables/flowers categories).
All the layers have been hand-painted in acrylics on paper and digitally composed.
The background has a random HSV color.

As always a big thank you goes to Koei Ural - @KoeiUral for the huge help with the p5.js code!
